UPON RETURNING TO THE ARPT, THE PILOT DECIDED TO MAKE A FLY-BY. THE PILOT 
REPORTED THAT WHILE ON A MODIFIED DOWNWIND AT AN ALT OF APPROXIMATELY 50 FEET AGL, 
THE GLIDER WHICH HE WAS PILOTING ENCOUNTERED ADVERSE WINDS AND 
DOWNDRAFTS. CONTROL OF THE AIRCRAFT WAS LOST AND IT DESCENDED RAPIDLY TO 
GROUND CONTACT. 
